Entries.default: "Does the Gullet lack? The seasons play havoc on our crops, I say." She frowns, waving you on.
"Between the rotten food piles and the scarcity, the Gullet barely supports life."
"If I wanted an emotional opinion, I would go to Periki's Overlook."
"Speak to my brother, Aruihi. He handles local concerns while I lose sleep over the archipelago." She beckons toward the exit.
"Careful." The air around Onekaza cools significantly.
"Every day that my people wake up to the sound of birds instead of cannon fire, I am feeding them. When they walk to a market at a leisurely pace, I am feeding them."
